cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the sample quality of generative adversarial nets (GANs) through the use of class labels and associated losses. As such, it is likely to fall under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as well as "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) since the experiments are conducted on image datasets. Additionally, the paper proposes a new metric for evaluating sample quality, which could place it under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The mathematical analysis of the properties of GANs also suggests a potential fit for "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and "cs.GR" (Graphics).
